title: Cake
lyrics:
You sugarcoat our situation
Got me waiting anticipation
When you gonna call, when you gonna call me?
No double dipping, you got it twisted
I’m not the kinda girl that’s gonna get addicted to vanilla



You can’t have it both ways

Boy it’s not your birthday

So get out, get out



You can’t have your cake and eat it too

You can’t have your cake and eat it too

Ain’t no secret you got a weakness for my sweetness

But you can’t have your cake and eat it too



Those other girls taste nothing like me

Eat your heart out just like candy

You’re not gonna call, but I know you want me



You can’t have it both ways

Boy it’s not your birthday

So get out, get out



You can’t have your cake and eat it too

You can’t have your cake and eat it too

Ain’t no secret you got a weakness for my sweetness

But you can’t have your cake and eat it too



I’m gonna blow out all your candles

I’m gonna blow out all your candles
